WEBVTT

02:00.000 --> 02:03.000
Sliver.1993.720p.BluRay.x264.YIFY

03:06.687 --> 03:07.812
Hi.

03:36.299 --> 03:38.426
- Good morning.
- Hello, I'm Carla Norris.

03:38.635 --> 03:40.136
I have an appointment
with Mrs. McEvoy.

03:40.303 --> 03:43.097
Through the garden, please.
I'll tell her you're on your way there.

03:43.265 --> 03:44.306
Thanks.

03:44.516 --> 03:48.018
Hello, Mrs. McEvoy?
Your 8:00 is here.

04:24.598 --> 04:26.348
- Good morning.
- Miss Norris?

04:26.558 --> 04:27.641
Yes.

04:27.851 --> 04:30.770
- Hello, I'm Evelyn McEvoy.
- Oh, I'm sorry I'm late.

04:31.188 --> 04:33.606
This midtown traffic.
I'll never get used to it.

04:33.815 --> 04:35.232
Shall we see the apartment?

04:37.360 --> 04:38.736
Yes. Sure.

04:45.577 --> 04:50.331
Central air conditioning.
Absolutely terrific kitchen.

04:51.708 --> 04:55.586
- I love the view.
- Yes. It's an airy place.

05:16.274 --> 05:18.275
What is it that you do, Miss Norris?

05:19.027 --> 05:20.903
I'm a book editor at Sutton.

05:24.074 --> 05:26.951
- What a strange tub.
- I like tubs myself.

05:29.704 --> 05:33.415
This is a nice room for reading, isn't it?

05:34.209 --> 05:35.918
- For reading?
- Hmm.

05:36.127 --> 05:38.128
Yes, it is, isn't it?

05:44.302 --> 05:46.428
l've got two tickets for Pavarotti Friday.

05:46.972 --> 05:48.597
I hate Pavarotti.

05:49.307 --> 05:54.228
I don't care if l ever go to an opera
for the rest of my life. Or the ballet.

05:55.188 --> 05:57.690
What do you want me to do?
Meet another charming man...

05:57.899 --> 06:00.276
...like Derek,
and wake up seven years later...

06:00.485 --> 06:03.028
- ...and realize I have no life?
- God, Carly, please.

06:03.488 --> 06:06.490
- Look, why don't you get tickets to....
- Who?

06:07.868 --> 06:10.077
- Pearl Jam.
- Pearl Jam?

06:10.287 --> 06:11.328
Yeah.

06:11.955 --> 06:13.414
You know, you're being a putz.

06:13.623 --> 06:16.417
How am I going to meet any attractive men
by myself?

06:16.626 --> 06:18.127
You love Pavarotti.

06:18.753 --> 06:21.839
I am a putz.
I wasted seven years of my life.

06:22.674 --> 06:26.176
- And I hate Pavarotti.
- Will you stop it?

06:26.386 --> 06:30.681
You are ready for new adventures.
New horizons. New lovers. New orgasms.

06:31.099 --> 06:34.059
- Well?
- Heh, I'm 35, I’m not 25.

06:34.603 --> 06:37.479
I don't need a date,
I need a relationship.

06:37.689 --> 06:40.024
Preferably one
where something happens this time.

06:40.233 --> 06:42.192
Sure, in case you've forgotten
how it works...

06:42.402 --> 06:44.612
...first you meet somebody,
then you have a relationship.

06:44.821 --> 06:46.280
Ooh, thank you, Dr. Ruth.

06:46.489 --> 06:49.825
Do you work here, or do you go
from office to office, offering advice?

06:50.076 --> 06:52.953
Will you look at chapter six?
I think I might have cut too deep.

06:53.163 --> 06:56.248
- You didn't show it to the author yet, did you?
- Yeah, l did.

06:57.250 --> 06:58.334
And?

06:58.710 --> 07:00.753
He said, "I'll discuss it with Carly."

07:00.962 --> 07:02.713
Heh, you cut too deep.

07:02.923 --> 07:05.466
Never show it to the author
before you give it to me first.

07:05.842 --> 07:07.551
- Sorry.
- It's okay.

07:07.928 --> 07:09.386
I'm sure the cuts are good.

07:09.679 --> 07:12.514
The author's a pussycat,
don't worry about it. This is good.

07:12.724 --> 07:15.976
Where are you with the James Dean bio?
Marketing wants to up the publishing date.

07:16.186 --> 07:19.146
- I'll be done by the end of the weekend.
- You're a genius, Carly.

07:19.356 --> 07:21.649
Sure, who wouldn't be
on your social schedule?

07:21.858 --> 07:24.360
Mrs. McEvoy on Line one.
She says it's important.

07:24.569 --> 07:26.445
- Do you want to talk to her?
- Yeah.

07:26.655 --> 07:30.616
And Mr. Parsons called. He wants
to take you to lunch at L'Adagio.

07:31.701 --> 07:33.535
That means I'm not getting my raise.

07:35.330 --> 07:36.372
Mrs. McEvoy.

07:36.581 --> 07:37.623
Good news, my dear.

07:37.832 --> 07:40.084
- Your application's been approved.
- Already?

07:40.752 --> 07:43.462
- ls that a problem?
- No.

07:44.255 --> 07:47.925
No, I.... I just didn't think
it would happen this fast.

07:48.760 --> 07:50.678
Oh, I thought you'd be pleased.

07:51.554 --> 07:55.516
I am. I'm very excited. Thank you.

07:55.684 --> 07:58.852
Well, then, we can get you in next week.

07:59.187 --> 08:01.689
- Next week will be fine.
- Splendid.

08:02.023 --> 08:04.650
- Goodbye.
- Bye.

08:34.014 --> 08:35.847
- There you go.
- Thank you.

08:36.057 --> 08:37.140
Sure.

08:37.642 --> 08:40.727
Sorry I couldn’t get the door
for you, Miss Norris.

08:40.937 --> 08:42.980
The movers will be here
in about an hour.

08:43.188 --> 08:46.442
- I'll keep an eye out for you.
- Thank you.

08:48.278 --> 08:52.531
He didn't want a "thank you."
I think he wanted a tip.

08:53.199 --> 08:56.452
Well, he didn't get the door for me,
now, did he?

08:56.995 --> 08:58.454
Sure he didn't.

08:58.872 --> 09:00.914
- Can I take one of these for you?
- I'm okay.

09:01.124 --> 09:03.542
Come on, I've got two free arms.

09:05.128 --> 09:06.670
You want me to take this other one for you?

09:06.880 --> 09:08.839
- No, I'm okay.
- You're sure?

09:09.466 --> 09:11.008
Okay.

09:14.804 --> 09:17.014
I, uh, know the neighborhood
real well, so...

09:17.223 --> 09:19.975
...if you want the lowdown
on stores and things like that.

09:20.185 --> 09:23.312
- I could....
- How's the market across the street?

09:23.521 --> 09:26.273
It's okay.
The one over on 39th is cheaper.

09:26.483 --> 09:27.524
Oh, heh, thanks.

09:27.734 --> 09:29.985
I'm not gonna ask again
if l can bring this for you.

09:30.195 --> 09:33.697
- Good. Don't.
- Here you go.

09:35.617 --> 09:36.992
Thank you.

09:37.202 --> 09:39.870
Welcome to 113. You'll like it here.

09:40.288 --> 09:42.039
I will. Thank you.

09:46.544 --> 09:49.296
You're right. These are getting heavy.

09:49.714 --> 09:52.591
- Sorry. I’ll see you.
- Bye.

09:55.053 --> 09:57.596
I need a check, okay, Register 3.

09:58.264 --> 10:01.850
Check, okay, on Register 3, please.

10:14.280 --> 10:16.448
You only have one thing.
Why don't you go ahead?

10:16.783 --> 10:18.575
Oh, good idea. Thanks.

10:19.619 --> 10:22.162
Um, I’m Gus Hale.

10:22.747 --> 10:24.915
- You're moving in today, aren't you?
- Mm-hm.

10:25.125 --> 10:27.709
- Well, welcome to 113.
- Thanks.

10:28.628 --> 10:31.713
Um, I’m in 23-B.

10:36.177 --> 10:38.470
- I'll take that for you.
- Thank you.

10:39.931 --> 10:41.431
Hey, why are you walking here?

10:46.604 --> 10:49.731
Forgive me,
I don't usually follow women around.

10:49.941 --> 10:52.192
I'm not a dirty old man, really not.

10:52.402 --> 10:57.114
- Are you certain?
- Sometimes I wish I were, but I'm not.

10:57.282 --> 11:00.868
- Why do you wish you were?
- Because it's boring when you're not.

11:01.077 --> 11:05.455
You just really....
Well, you look like someone.

11:06.332 --> 11:08.500
Someone you like
or someone you dislike?

11:08.710 --> 11:10.627
Oh, no. l liked her a lot.

11:10.837 --> 11:12.963
What's really strange is...

11:13.506 --> 11:15.549
...she was in 20-B as well.

11:16.134 --> 11:17.801
Naomi Singer.

11:17.969 --> 11:22.222
- When did she move?
- Well, she didn't. She....

11:22.390 --> 11:25.559
She jumped out the window.

11:27.187 --> 11:32.482
Uh, I'm sorry, I didn't mean to, ugh....
I've never had much goddamned tact.

11:32.984 --> 11:36.862
Ugh, I tell you what.
I'm about to go off to Japan.

11:37.238 --> 11:40.115
Perhaps when I get back,
I can fill you in on all the gossip.

11:40.325 --> 11:43.202
- What are you gonna do there?
- I teach a class at NYU.

11:43.703 --> 11:46.121
The Psychology of the Lens.

11:46.581 --> 11:49.625
- "The Psychology of the Lens," heh-heh-heh.
- Yes.

11:49.959 --> 11:53.253
I teach all aspects.
I mean, cameras, camcorders....

11:53.463 --> 11:55.631
I'm going
to look at the latest technology.

11:58.176 --> 12:00.636
So you like salacious gossip?

12:01.262 --> 12:03.680
I make a great cappuccino too.

12:04.015 --> 12:05.140
Call me.

12:05.350 --> 12:08.435
How can I call you
when I don't even know your name?

12:08.686 --> 12:11.772
How can you not know my name
if you knew my apartment number?

12:11.981 --> 12:17.152
Our doormen are spoiled.
Five bucks only gets you half the information.

12:17.820 --> 12:20.822
- Carly Norris.
- Ah.

12:21.532 --> 12:23.867
Must have liked her an awful lot
to spend five bucks.

12:24.035 --> 12:25.369
I did.

12:25.536 --> 12:29.623
We were pals.

14:29.494 --> 14:30.994
How's the market across the street?

14:31.204 --> 14:32.329
It's okay.

14:41.756 --> 14:44.841
Welcome to 113. You'll like it here.

16:15.349 --> 16:18.101
- Where do you live now?
- ln the village.

16:19.562 --> 16:21.605
This will be quite a change.

16:23.107 --> 16:25.317
Shall l show you the rest of the apartment?

16:25.526 --> 16:27.736
Have you grown tired of the village?

16:28.279 --> 16:31.448
Oh, I teach all aspects of it.
Cameras, camcorders....

16:56.682 --> 16:57.933
This way.

16:58.142 --> 17:00.477
Now, why don't you talk
to Lynn Nesbit about him?

17:00.686 --> 17:04.606
His last book didn't sell very well.
Perhaps he's getting itchy at Random.

17:04.815 --> 17:08.568
Perhaps he's blaming their marketing
and not the thinness of his characters.

17:08.903 --> 17:11.946
Perhaps you can convince Lynn
to alert him to the inadequacies...

17:12.156 --> 17:14.699
- ...of their marketing department.
- Are we negotiating?

17:14.909 --> 17:16.242
I wouldn't call it that.

17:20.665 --> 17:22.082
Attractive man, isn't he?

17:22.415 --> 17:27.712
Alex, I ask you for a raise,
you take me out to lunch and try to set me up.

17:28.214 --> 17:29.673
Jack Landsford.

17:29.882 --> 17:33.093
Shred of Evidence, Flesh and Blood,
police procedurals.

17:33.302 --> 17:35.595
He hasn't written anything
in five or six years...

17:35.805 --> 17:38.598
...but he made so much off of
Flesh and Blood, he doesn't have to.

17:38.849 --> 17:40.600
He's got a ranch in Montana.

17:40.810 --> 17:43.520
- And speak of the devil,
- Hello, Alex.

17:43.729 --> 17:45.689
- How are you?
- All right, heh.

17:46.190 --> 17:47.440
I'm the devil.

17:49.026 --> 17:51.194
- Carla Norris.
- Hello.

17:52.697 --> 17:53.905
You look familiar to me.

17:54.907 --> 17:57.284
Maybe that's because
I live in your building.

17:58.869 --> 18:00.287
- Oh, yeah.
- Heh.

18:00.496 --> 18:02.664
- Jack, Carly is a big fan of yours.
- Mm.

18:02.873 --> 18:04.791
She just loved Flesh and Blood.

18:05.001 --> 18:07.127
- Hey.
- I haven't read it.

18:08.087 --> 18:09.462
I'm sorry.

18:10.131 --> 18:12.173
- Here you are.
- She hasn't read me.

18:13.551 --> 18:16.511
Alex, why is it she hasn't read me?

18:16.721 --> 18:19.848
Everybody's read me, heh.
I'm easy to read.

18:20.057 --> 18:22.976
- I haven't.
- She has better taste than I thought.

18:26.564 --> 18:27.647
She’ll read me, though.

18:28.190 --> 18:30.275
What if she doesn't like
what she reads?

18:30.610 --> 18:31.860
- Hi, Jack.
- You’ll read me.

18:35.281 --> 18:39.117
I know you'll read me.
Because you have good taste.

18:41.537 --> 18:44.247
You've lost her now, Jack.
She likes being in control.

18:45.750 --> 18:46.875
So do l.

18:48.419 --> 18:51.129
- See you around the neighborhood.
- Yeah.

18:53.591 --> 18:54.758
Alex.

18:58.679 --> 19:02.182
I spend seven years in a bad marriage,
and you say I like being in control?

19:02.642 --> 19:04.267
But you ended it, didn't you?

19:12.693 --> 19:15.862
No. No way.

19:16.614 --> 19:17.697
No.

19:18.616 --> 19:21.701
Fuck both of you. You said 700, Mike.

19:22.495 --> 19:25.538
Yeah, l know it's not fucking Vogue.
So what?

19:26.624 --> 19:28.583
Well, it's your choice.

19:28.793 --> 19:34.297
Look, I’m hungry, I'm jet-lagged, and
I don't need this shit. Goodbye, Michael.

19:34.465 --> 19:37.717
God, I'm sorry. I’m gonna get those
right out of your way.

19:37.885 --> 19:39.177
- That's okay.
- I'm Vida.

19:39.387 --> 19:40.428
- Carly Norris.
- Hi.

19:40.638 --> 19:42.138
- I'll give you a hand.
- Thanks.

19:43.224 --> 19:46.393
Damn doormen.
I really tip them well too.

19:46.727 --> 19:47.977
Everybody does.

19:48.187 --> 19:50.146
They're never around
when you need them.

19:50.356 --> 19:52.982
You're right.
You should see them at Christmas.

19:53.192 --> 19:54.901
Like flies on shit then.

19:57.655 --> 19:59.614
Oh, yeah, this guy was here.

19:59.824 --> 20:04.661
He left this for you.

20:11.585 --> 20:15.088
- You're all moved in, then?
- Oh, God, no. l hate it.

20:15.297 --> 20:18.174
I know. It's worse than anal intercourse.

20:19.635 --> 20:21.553
- You look like--
- Yeah, the girl that....

20:21.762 --> 20:22.804
- Naomi.
- Yeah.

20:23.013 --> 20:25.515
Somebody's already told you.
I guess they would have.

20:25.725 --> 20:28.143
- Were you friends?
- Well, sort of.

20:28.394 --> 20:30.603
I mean, she was only here about a year.

20:30.813 --> 20:32.856
And most of that time, I was in Milan.

20:33.065 --> 20:34.691
Ass-pinching Italians.

20:34.900 --> 20:37.026
- Ugh.
- My bum is still blue.

20:37.445 --> 20:39.195
I couldn't believe it, though.

20:39.405 --> 20:42.365
I mean,
she just didn't seem like the type.

20:42.992 --> 20:44.492
- Were you here when she--
- Yeah.

20:44.702 --> 20:47.370
She came over
to borrow some coffee the night before.

20:47.580 --> 20:50.373
- I didn't have any.
- Caffeine withdrawal.

20:50.750 --> 20:51.875
That would do it to me.

20:53.836 --> 20:57.130
That's my agent. He's a slimy bastard.

21:01.552 --> 21:04.137
Just a goddamned second,
all right, Michael?

21:05.014 --> 21:06.473
Hey. Thanks.

21:06.682 --> 21:08.308
Right. So see you around.

21:08.517 --> 21:11.811
If you ever need any coffee
or anything....

21:11.979 --> 21:14.481
Just make sure you don't run out.

21:15.983 --> 21:19.319
Mr. Brown. That's original.
And where's he staying?

21:20.529 --> 21:22.906
The Regency Arms?

21:23.073 --> 21:24.657
Okay.

21:25.493 --> 21:28.703
And, uh, what's his room number?

21:30.372 --> 21:34.542
627, got it.

21:35.169 --> 21:38.046
Yeah, well, they all say
they're producers or sheikhs.

21:38.255 --> 21:41.841
Hi, putz.
I’m giving you your last chance for Pavarotti.

21:42.092 --> 21:45.512
Hey, isn't Pearl Jam
some sort of oriental sex thing?

21:45.721 --> 21:47.514
Yummy.

21:51.060 --> 21:53.269
Carla, this is Zeke Hawkins calling.

21:53.437 --> 21:55.688
I, uh, hope you remember me.

21:55.898 --> 21:57.315
l live in the building too.

21:57.525 --> 21:59.818
We met when you were
moving in last weekend?

22:00.027 --> 22:03.154
Anyway, listen, um, l was just calling
to let you know that if you...

22:03.364 --> 22:06.866
...need any help with anything,
l've got some pull with the manager, so...

22:07.076 --> 22:08.785
...don't be afraid to give me a call.

22:08.994 --> 22:13.540
I’m at home most of the day.
My number's 5553126.

22:13.707 --> 22:16.543
All righty? Okay, bye.

22:16.710 --> 22:17.836
Hi, it's Peter.

22:18.045 --> 22:20.129
We are moving up the pub date
on the Dean book.

22:20.339 --> 22:23.132
Just thought I’d call
and let you know. Bye.

23:07.595 --> 23:10.972
Yeah, but what about
the appointment with Sony in Osaka?

23:11.181 --> 23:13.308
Seven thirty on Monday?

23:13.934 --> 23:16.728
Oh, well. I'll do it any time they will.

23:16.937 --> 23:19.355
I mean, I have to see them.
They're state-of-the-art.

23:19.607 --> 23:21.858
...defensive system
is extraordinarily developed.

23:22.067 --> 23:23.943
Acute schizophrenic, non-paranoid.

23:24.153 --> 23:26.029
Classic Jekyll-and-Hyde syndrome.

23:26.238 --> 23:29.032
Clearly a great danger to women.

23:29.241 --> 23:32.035
No, no, no. It's so good to hear your voice.

23:35.247 --> 23:36.789
We could rent one.

23:36.957 --> 23:38.499
Well, that's an idea.

23:38.709 --> 23:40.627
Hi, Zeke. It's Carla Norris.

23:40.794 --> 23:43.963
Thanks for your call. l, uh, heh....

23:44.131 --> 23:46.841
lf l ever get unpacked around here...

23:47.051 --> 23:52.388
...l was thinking of having, um,
a cocktail party on Friday night.

23:52.806 --> 23:55.642
Um, sometime after 6:00 o’clock.

23:55.809 --> 23:59.187
And I was wondering
if you'd like to come.

23:59.396 --> 24:03.566
Okay, I hope that you do. Bye-bye.

24:12.952 --> 24:14.118
Brother.

25:23.230 --> 25:24.731
- You think that was funny?
- Yeah.

25:24.940 --> 25:27.567
I didn't think that was funny.
You scared the shit out of me.

25:27.776 --> 25:29.027
Yeah, yeah, I know. I know.

25:30.487 --> 25:33.239
Ah, I'm sorry.
You're right, it wasn't funny. l....

25:33.449 --> 25:36.325
It was a real dumb-ass thing to do.
Really, I'm sorry.

25:37.828 --> 25:40.079
Can we start over again, huh?

25:40.289 --> 25:45.293
Heh, what for? I really don't see the point.

25:45.461 --> 25:47.545
- Hey, did you get the books?
- Yeah.

25:47.755 --> 25:49.464
- Did you read them?
- No.

25:49.673 --> 25:52.300
Oh, yeah, you did. You can't fool me.

25:52.509 --> 25:54.177
I read a few pages of one of them.

25:54.386 --> 25:57.013
Uh-huh. You read both.
You couldn’t put them down.

25:57.222 --> 25:58.973
I'm right, aren't I? Tell me I am right.

25:59.183 --> 26:00.224
You're wrong.

26:00.809 --> 26:01.893
What?

26:02.102 --> 26:04.687
You don't like sex and violence?
It sells, you know.

26:04.897 --> 26:07.190
It buys ranches in Montana, I'm told.

26:07.399 --> 26:10.860
Oh-ho-ho-ho. You've been checking on me.
I like that.

26:12.529 --> 26:14.155
- Thank you.
- For what?

26:14.364 --> 26:16.074
For stopping.

26:16.241 --> 26:20.578
Now, how about gossip?
About James Dean, for instance.

26:20.788 --> 26:22.747
Doesn't that sell?

26:22.915 --> 26:24.999
You've been checking on me.
I don't like that.

26:25.209 --> 26:28.503
I hear you're, uh, very good at the tell-alls.

26:28.670 --> 26:31.756
I guess that comes
from being married to a very boring guy.

26:31.965 --> 26:33.674
You just like all the juicy talk.

26:33.884 --> 26:36.511
- Fuck you.
- Would you like to?

26:36.678 --> 26:39.597
I can try and make myself available.
Hey, look....

26:39.807 --> 26:41.808
I'm a writer. People tell me secrets...

26:42.017 --> 26:44.769
...and I just take notes.
Like Truman Capote.

26:45.062 --> 26:47.939
- You could tell me your secrets.
- I don't have any secrets.

26:49.858 --> 26:50.942
Sure you do.

26:52.277 --> 26:54.028
What secrets do I have?

26:56.740 --> 26:57.949
I'd never tell.

27:03.122 --> 27:04.539
Did you send me the telescope?

27:07.209 --> 27:09.877
- Telescope?
- Yeah.

27:10.087 --> 27:12.547
Why would I send you a telescope?

27:12.714 --> 27:13.714
Hey.

27:17.469 --> 27:19.679
I can't keep up with you.

27:20.055 --> 27:21.973
No, you can't.

27:26.311 --> 27:27.478
Taxi.

27:46.582 --> 27:49.792
